z.kable <- function(t, ...) { 
  knitr::kable(t, format = "html", ...) %>% 
    kableExtra::kable_styling(bootstrap_options = "striped",full_width = T)
}

inx <- function(data, inp.n) { # data: current dataframe; inp.n: position for non-inputs
  # numeric input indicator
  num <- sapply(data, is.numeric)
  num[inp.n] <- FALSE

  # nominal input indicator
  cat <- sapply(data, is.factor)
  cat[inp.n] <- FALSE

  # missing value indicator
  na <- sapply(data,function(x) any(is.na(x)))
  na[inp.n] <- FALSE

  data.frame(num, cat, na)
}

z.predclass <- function(predicted.probs, y = GoldMarket$S){
  pi <- as.numeric(prop.table(table(y))) # observed strata/proportion in the responce
  diffpred <- predicted.probs - pi # difference in predicted probability and obs strata/proportion
  maxclass <- apply(diffpred, 1, function(x) which.max(x)) # index for class of each predicted prob
  return(factor(maxclass, levels = as.character(1:5), labels = levels(y)))
}

z.fscore <- function(t){
  # t                                     # contingicy table(predicted, actual)
  # t*diag(5)                             # True Positives / correct fits(predictions)
  # diag(t)                               # True Positives as a vector
  # margin.table(t,2)                     # ( TP + FP) for each class
  sensitivity = diag(t)/margin.table(t,2) # % of actual correctly predicted 
  
  # diag(t)                               # True Negitive (multiclass aprocch?) as a vector
  # margin.table(t,1)                     # ( TN + FN) for each class
  precision = diag(t)/margin.table(t,1)   # % correctly predicted of predicted
  
  # F score = harmonic mean of Sensitivity and Precision
  fscore = 2 / (sensitivity^-1 + precision^-1 )
  
  out = cbind(rbind(sensitivity, precision, fscore),
              margin.table(rbind(sensitivity, precision, fscore),1)/5)
  colnames(out)[6] <- "ClassMean"
  return(out)
}

z.raocoef <- function(stepS.all.1){ # score test coefficients
  invisible(capture.output(s <- summary(stepS.all.1)))
  suppressWarnings(capture.output(rao.score <- score.stat(
    vglm(as.formula(stepS.all.1[["call"]][["formula"]]),
         family=cumulative(parallel=T),
         data=GoldMarket), omit1s = F, all.out = T)
  ))
  d <- data.frame(s[["coefficients"]]) %>%
     rownames_to_column("Coefficients") %>%
     dplyr::select(Parameter = Coefficients,
                   Estimate = Value) %>%
     add_column(SE = rao.score$SE0[c(5:length(rao.score$score.stat),1:4)],
                Score.Stat = rao.score$score.stat[c(5:length(rao.score$score.stat),1:4)],
                c = c(rep(-1,length(rao.score$score.stat)-4), rep(1,4))) %>%
     mutate(Estimate = c*Estimate,
            Score.Stat = Score.Stat*Score.Stat,
            Pr.Chi = pchisq(Score.Stat,1, lower.tail = FALSE)) %>% 
    dplyr::select(-c)
  knitr::kable(d[c((dim(d)[1]-3):dim(d)[1],1:(dim(d)[1]-4)),], format="html",
               caption = "Analysis of Maximum Likelihood Estimates",
               digits = 4, row.names = F) %>% 
    kableExtra::kable_styling(bootstrap_options = "striped",full_width = F)
}

z.globaltest <- function(stepS.all.1){ # LRT of global hypothesis
  invisible(capture.output(a <- anova(update(stepS.all.1, .~1), stepS.all.1)))
  knitr::kable(data.frame(Test = c("Likelihood Test"),
                          Chi.Square = a$`LR stat.`[2],
                          DF = a$`   Df`[2],
                          Pr.Chi = a$`Pr(Chi)`[2]),
               caption = "Global Test Null Hypothesis: BETA=0", digits = 4) %>% 
    kableExtra::kable_styling(bootstrap_options = "striped",full_width = F)
}

z.ore <- function(stepS.all.1){ # Odds Ratio Estimates
  invisible(capture.output(pr <- profile(stepS.all.1)))
  knitr::kable(data.frame(Effect = attributes(pr)[["names"]],
                          Point.Estimate = 1/exp(attributes(pr)[["original.fit"]][["coefficients"]]),
                          conf.low =  1/exp(confint(pr)[,2]),
                          conf.high =  1/exp(confint(pr)[,1])),
               caption = "Odds Ratio Estimates", digits = 4, row.names = F) %>% 
    kableExtra::kable_styling(bootstrap_options = "striped",full_width = F)
}

z.mfs <- function(stepS.all.1){ # Model Fit Statistics
  knitr::kable(data.frame(Criterion = c("AIC", "BIC", "Deviance"),
                          Intercept.Only = c(AIC(update(stepS.all.1, .~1)), 
                                             BIC(update(stepS.all.1, .~1)), 
                                             deviance(update(stepS.all.1, .~1))),
                          Intercept.Covariates = c(AIC(stepS.all.1), 
                                                   BIC(stepS.all.1), 
                                                   deviance(stepS.all.1))),
               caption = "Model Fit Statistics", digits = 2, row.names = F) %>% 
    kableExtra::kable_styling(bootstrap_options = "striped",full_width = F)
}

Gold Market Analysis:

  • The Stock market is generally divided into three most markets:
    • Bear Market, Shock Market, and Bull Market
Y: The return rate of international gold market (XAUUSD) closing price (cp) on every trading day 
    - y_i = (cp_i-cp_{i-1})/(cp_i)*100: % change in daily gold market price 
        * The XAUUSD refers to the price of 1 troy ounce of gold in terms of the US dollar
        * i in trading days for 2018-2019 (US & China market)
S: Y classified to 5 factors
    - S1 = -2, if y <= -1.5%: "mad bear market" the gold index decreases significantly
    - S2 = -1, if -1.5% < y <= -0.5%: "bear market" the gold index declines slowly
    - S3 = 0, if -0.5% < y <= 0.5%: "shock market" the gold index fluctuates in small scope
    - S4 = 1, if 0.5% < y <= 1.5%: "bull market" the gold index increases mildly
    - S5 = 2, if y >= 1.5%: "mad bull market" the gold index increases significantly
St: Tomorrows state of the international gold market
X1: US Dollar Index (DXY) daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%) 
X2: United States 3-Month Bond Yield daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%)
X3: United States 2-Year Bond Yield daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%) 
X4: United States 5-Year Bond Yield daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%)
X5: United States 10-Year Bond Yield daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%)
X6: United States 30-Year Bond Yield daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%) 
X7: Dow Jones daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%)
X8: Dow Jones Shanghai daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%) 
X9: FTSE China A50 daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%)
X10: Hang Seng daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%)
X11: NAS DAQ daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%) 
X12: SP 500 daily 
    - Date  Price(close), Open, High, Low, Change(%)
X13: US Federal Interest Rate 
    - Date  Change(%)

GoldMarket <- Dat$Gold %>% 
  filter(Date >= as.Date("2016-12-30") & Date <= as.Date("2019-12-31")) %>% 
  left_join(dplyr::select(Dat$US_Dollar_Index, Date, US_Dollar_Index = Change, High, Low),
            by = c("Date")) %>% 
  mutate(US_Dollar_Index_HL = High-Low) %>% 
  dplyr::select(-High,-Low) %>%
  left_join(dplyr::select(Dat$US_Dollar_Index_Futures, Date, US_Dollar_Index_Futures = Change, 
                          High, Low),
            by = c("Date")) %>% 
  mutate(US_Dollar_Index_FHL = High-Low) %>%

            by = c("Date")) %>%
